The paper deals with questions related to computability theory, which is a subfield of theoretical computer science. The concepts of compression and ranking functions are related to complexity theory, but the paper focuses on their recursion-theoretic versions. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also deals with lexicographical ordering, which falls under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also mentions the notion of 1-truth-table degrees, which is related to the theory of computability and falls under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper mentions the concept of information theory, which falls under cs.IT (Information Theory).
